    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="381"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d381">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/336.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consular Agent <persName type="from">Hedian</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Esmeraldas</hi>
                        </placeName>, [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-outside-research"
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>
                        <hi rend="italic">; received February 10, 1914</hi>].</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Commander Government forces notifies Consul Esmeraldas will bombard city to-day
                    5.50. If not prevented suffering noncombatants will be horrible. No facilities
                    available to leave. Useless destruction property will cause destitution which
                    will require outside help. Warship desirable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hedian</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
